  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Sustainable Partnerships for Economic Recovery (Prosper)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An Integrated, Community Based Approach for four targeted communities in Kohso/Dereshe and Surma/Maji Districts, Ethiopia. Mercy Corps Ethiopia believes that there are four key integrated areas that, when implemented together, will have a maximum impact on beneficiary communities&#x2019; ability to become self-supporting and self-sustaining. These four areas are: 
1) Health, water, and sanitation;
 -Reproductive Health, Hygiene Promotion, and Nutrition Trainings
 -Community Water Project
 -Water and Sanitation at Primary Schools
2) Livelihoods diversification and improvement;
 -Women&#x2019;s Groups as a means of diversifying and improving women&#x2019;s livelihoods
 -Legal Rights Training for Women
 -Child Psycho-Social Protection
3) Environmental management;
 -Energy Efficient Stoves
4) Education
 -Upgraded facilities and supplies for four primary schools
 -Establishment of four Alternative Basic Education Centres
Mercy Corps views all four areas through gender focused and conflict sensitive lenses.</narrative>
  </description>
